<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-09-29T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-09-29T00:00:00-05:00" n="1523" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1523">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.404/99.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Vice Consul <persName type="from">Stadden</persName>
                                to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Manzanillo</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-09-29">
                                    <hi rend="italic">September 29, 1915</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>The military authorities in Colima have confiscated Catholic church,
                            orphan asylum, colleges, and have given fifteen days for the bishop to
                            evacuate his palace. These desecrations of church property are causing
                            great indignation.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Stadden</hi>.</signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>